Anyone who passes up the opportunity to take his class is doing themselves a massive disservice.
Incredible professor. Very knowledgeble and helpful. Best scholar at Stanford PS. His class is a MUST.

There's a lot of reading, but it's worth it, because Diamond's passion for the subject (democracy) makes everyone in the room want to know more. If you ever have a question, he'll take the time to answer it (sometimes so much time that he doesn't finish his lectures because he answers so many student questions!). Brilliant professor, great class.
Just great, kind, helpful, a world citizen open to new ideas. An acquired taste and definitely requires listening stamina, but well worth it.
A fantastic conversationalist and wonderfully generous and genius teacher. My favorite one of all time. But I don't like football.
great brilliant helpful charming teacher
Noah is very passionate about organic chemistry and explains it very well and clearly. His office hours are enlightening and his dog is very cute.
Tough class lead by excellent professors.
This class was horrible, I have to retake it but I have NO REGRETS because Noah is life.
great teacher. great course.
jurafsky and ramscar are a great team. the most compelling class i've taken at stanford.

Worth it. First investing course for me. Not a math person. This class made a lot of what used to confuse me about money very understandable. Prof listens well and makes good remarks that help to make the material easier to understand. It's an internet course, but it felt closer than that. The book is very good.

Highly recommended. Marshall teaches an online course in Stanford's Continuing Studies program. Knowledgeable, empathetic, and highly motivating. This course was not inexpensive, but it was a good value.

He's an amicable professor who is very passionate about his teachings. Some lectures by him are very fascinating, while seemed a bit like filler. However, overall, I really enjoyed the readings for this class, its overall content, and how low-key it was. Adam expects you to be creative and get the work done, but its never too challenging.

comment: Great lecturer. Lowkey has a savior complex though. Pretty good class- wouldnt take it again. Seems like more work than other THINK classes.

Adam is a Pulitzer Prize winner. His class--Stories Everywhere--requires lots of reading, but little to no analytical writing--instead the class is designed so students absorb different writing styles and experiment with them on their own. Only two graded projects besides participation. Adam is hilarious and made me want to show up to class.
Unable to grasp basic mathematical concepts
He was very hard to follow and made many mistakes. I wouldn't recommend taking Stats with him.
Taylor Rule is awesome.  Great Prof.
He doesn't answer questions in a satisfactory manner. He doesn't explain any concepts at all. Basically, you have to read the textbook and figure it all out yourself.
The lectures were very long and slow, very difficult tests

John Taylor is well-known in the field of economics. However, hes very old and the lectures are quite dry. No need to attend lectures at all, as the slides are all uploaded and he provides little explanation on top of the info already presented in the slides. Would probably skip any quarter with John Taylor and wait for a diff professor.

Prof. Jo Boaler's class has been the best Education methodology course that I have taken at Stanford. She presents her ideas in a clear manner and really pushes her students to critically examine what we take for granted as researchers. Even if you have no interest in math, I think any budding researcher can benefit from taking this course with Jo.

Jo chose incredibly helpful readings for this course. I learned important fundamentals about research in math education from this class. We also had interesting and insightful discussions, and the research project and paper we had to do for the class were very very useful.

Professor Boaler had a fast-paced, challenging course. She really kept it interesting and we did a variety of exercises and we had a variety of assessments. She was available outside of class, as well for consultation on our projects and papers.
No Comments
gautam is the man...plus he writes random linux utilities that make things transparent
Lecture goes fast . . . he really knows what he is talking about.  Very hard class, but he is really good at office hours.

I've taken two classes with Lisa. She is GENUINELY interested in what her students have to say and doesn't want to just lecture. Participate when you have something insightful to say. DO THE READING, as nothing will help you more. Great teacher. Brilliant, caring, and amazing! I'd definitely recommend her classes for a truly rewarding experience.

interesting class, great guy
Gerry Gast is the man!  By far the best professor from my 4 years at Stanford, and the man who set me on course for my current career!
Excellent teacher. Unbelievable breadth of knowledge. Accessible. Passion for topic.
Extremely knowledgable, but one of the most boring teachers I've ever had. I was in very small class (only 3 people), but he just spent the whole time lecturing in a monotone.

Extremely engaged. Enthusiastic.  Unbelievably knowledgeable, but still very approachable and relatable.  Experienced researcher and teacher.  Excellent lectures with appropriate and engaging multimedia. Helpful and avaiable during office hours. Do not miss.

So true! She is AMAZING. Take an introsem with her!!

Prof Tallent is BRILLIANT, interesting, well-spoken, kind, and just entirely badass.  To take one of her classes is to love her, and also to learn so freaking much.  My adoration knows no bounds, and I know I'm not the only one who feels this way.
Didn't actually think i would enter a field in economics but he really got to me and i am now working for experience as an economic at a Norwegian company :)
He is maybe a good economist, but ....

Knowledgeable and completely apathetic.  I would ask him very fundamental questions via email and he would never reply.  The only way to get a response seemed to be call or walk to his office directly.  His lectures were good but then he was off the clock.  He is probably tenured.
He is really really great.
great lecturer

Great professor! Extremely clear, funny, and makes the class worthwhile! :)

One of my favorite and most impactful professors -- I rarely take notes and found myself hastily recording his poetic words and profound insights.

To get this out of the way: I dare you find a more handsome professor at Stanford - not likely. Think Harrison Ford without the ruggedness. The powerful rhetoric, the persuasive arguments, the kindness, the gentle humor, the courage, the authenticity. I'm in love.

Feola is the best professor I've ever had.  All students should take his class especially if you enjoy participation and deep thinking. He's a really tough grader but always gives a FULL page of feedback on papers, making my writing miles better. He's super friendly and always looking to help, some people think he's crazy at first but stick with it

Very intelligent professor who fosters interesting class discussions. If you aren't into abstract, philosophical ideas, you won't enjoy his classes. Grades kind of harshly on papers, which count for a lot of your grade. Overall, he's a very good professor.
Feola is the absolute BEST IHUM teaching fellow--  no joke. Switch into his section at all costs. 2007-08 he TFed for Fate of Reason and Freedom, Equality, Difference.
lazy and passive teaching. takes a ton of shortcuts and tries to cover it up. beware of his charm, it's deceiving
He is so learned.

His textbook (which he wrote himself) is brilliantly clear. His lectures are incomprehensible. I never understood why there was such a difference.

Ditto what the other person said.  Clearly he's a world famous researcher.  His teaching though is incomprehensible.  Didn't learn a thing from 113, took 114 with Milgram, and everything suddenly made sense.

This was one of the hardest classes I've taken.  His lectures are worthless cause you can't understand anything he says.  Supposedly he is a genius- but in the research field.  I don't doubt that.  As an educator, he stinks.

This was a last minute class for me but I became completely absorbed by the professors ability to engage and challenge each member of the class. Might have been over my head but will be a class I remember for years. Want to be challenged--take this professor's classes.

rating_tags: Respected--Graded by few things--Accessible outside class

comment: Amy was so incredible as a professor and person. Not only was she very adept in her subject matter, but she also loved her students and met us where we were at. She was very caring, and often would email me checking in on me when something went awry in class, which happened a few times with my personal health and other classmates.
Great person but he would leave 80% of the lecture to do independent or group work (wouldn't teach). Overall an easy class though

John is a great lecturer. He covers contents clearly and thoroughly, prepares for lectures, and has amazing boardwork. His homeworks are well-designed and good practice to supplement the lectures. He also gives high grades to everyone. I recommend all courses taught by John!
Great course, clear instruction, impactful teaching style. Highly recommended for anyone looking to learn javascript. Way better than appacademy

Jason is probably the best teacher in the German department and definitely the best language teacher I have ever had. Class is usually interesting and fun. There is a quiz every Friday but no pop quizzes so you always know what to expect. He also doesn't give a midterm or final which is great. He is very helpful and really helps you learn German.
No Comments
Very entertaining and crazy,  in a good way. Highly recommend.

Dr. Menon is incredibly smart and approachable. She is really knowledgeable and still allows you to sit with the material and chew on it yourself. She's a great teacher.  I'm so excited that I took her class and look forward to taking more classes with her.  I would highly recommend any class taught by her. You won't regret it.
Best Japanese professor!

Took intro to mechatronics. One of the best classes I've ever taken. Learned a ton about mechanical engineering (had only done any EE and CS) which was so much fun. Come on, I got to cut designs with lazers! How could it not be a great class?  Ed offsets the huge amount of work by being a great great teacher.
he is really good new prof

Mr. Oberle is AMAZING! His lectures are clear and concise.  I feel the homework assigned and quizzes/exams given are right on. He was ALWAYS available for extra help. His "MATH" jokes are hilarious. I had a lot of personal difficulties this semester so I have to repeat Math26 but I made sure I got him again and created my schedule around his class.
Definitely recommend this guy! one of the nicest people i've ever met ????????~

Margot is one of my favorite teachers at Stanford. She has incredible real world experience with flow simulations and America's Cup yacht design, and is wonderful at explaining hard mathematical concepts in class. If you ever get the chance to take a CME class with her, DO IT!

Awesome professor.  Took two classes with her and declared a major in Comp Lit because of my experiences in her classes, which made me love Comparative Literature.  I learned so much from her.  Highly recommended!
Awesome.

An absolute dream! Engaging and responsive in and out of class. Excellent conversationalist and a brilliant lecturer. Most importantly, she really cares about each of her students a lot. She is not an inordinately tough professor, but you do have to put in the work, but her excellent teaching makes it very easy to be engaged with the classwork.

Will Monroe is awesome, patient, clear, super helpful and interesting. I'd taken probability and stats before but had never gotten such in-depth explanations of all the important ideas and how they relate to computers.  This is an essential course with a superstar teacher!

As a PWR and LSP teacher Dr JJ is pretty cool, she talks a lot about language and identity. She's also a cool person who had the last office hours at the climbing gym. She's a bit of a stickler for useless things tho, like whether you respond to certain emails or if you can exactly repeat the things she says according to her views.
Taught me how to lose but failed so I'm always winning. I had high hopes for this class, but they came crashing down after midterms. First test is a doozy.
Avoid if at all possible.
Shes great

I love Norah so much. She is the light of my life. She makes my Stanford experience worthwhile. Shout out to her amazing teaching. I will remember her forever

HW sets are a great complement to the lecture notes.
Due to his involvement in the industry he chooses very useful topics.

She's really friendly and interested in helping students understand.  It's challenging but the class is totally fun, easy if you actually go to class and do the work.  I would totally take this class again!

comment: She's OK, kinda boring, not a good ally, doesn't understand tech and gets salty if you try to help her with her mistakes.

PERFECT TEACHER. SHE IS LIKE THE  ARISTOTLE OF ECONOMICS. THE MICHAEL JORDAN OF MODERN ACADEMIA. THE ALLAH OF SUPPLY AND DEMAND. THE HOUDINI OF PROFESSORSHIP. THANKS FOR THE CLASS OF A LIFE TIME. I AM NOW A DOUBLE MAJOR IN ECONOMICS AND ECONOMICS.
Makes asymptotic analysis interesting and super easy to understand.  Kind professor with a positive attitude who cares about his students and makes the course accessible.

Professor Ge Wang is a total genius, probably the only Stanford professor who crosses the fuzzie-techie divide. He's a great, inspiration teacher who makes great art, is super nice, teaches amazing courses, and just wrote the most awesome and deep cross-genre book. I've never read any of my professors books for fun ever til now.
Was learning how to teach.

Ahoo is the best professor I've ever had. She genuinely cares about students' well-being above all else (which is rare). She understands that people learn in different ways. Going to class is an absolute joy and she gets right to the important stuff--so engaging. Being in her class made me excited about school for the first time in a long time.

Prof Fulton is spectacular! She always made time for me and helped take my writing to the next level. Great lectures. Careful though... If you don't show up for the mandatory conferences, you won't get a good grade on your TiC. I learned this the hard way. Still highly recommended.

comment: Very well organized. Expects a lot of participation. Wouldn't take again.

comment: Great teacher and mentor! Cute too!

Nice person overall. Answer your questions. But he could be more prepared for the lecture and assignment. The only good thing is that TA Micheal gives good tutorial session, which makes it up for the terrible lecture.

comment: Prof Anwar was remarkable! He makes the effort to get to know students through conferences and his feedback is very useful. Wants you to succeed and it shows through the lectures and class activities. Best writing class!

comment: Professor Culp was sensational. Her readings of the works we discussed in class were fascinating. She provided plenty of materials to help in being successful on assignments and was accessible and flexible too. Very manageable and thought provoking coursework. Would definitely take a course with her again if given the opportunity.
Super kind and wonderful lecturer :)

comment: Top-notch teacher, no debate. Didn't expect him to be so young but very very well respected and smart. You'll love his humor.
